# Risk Matrix — local development environment.
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and edit. `.env.local` is gitignored.
#
# Next.js auto-loads .env.local in dev. NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars are baked into
# the client bundle at build time, so changing them requires a dev-server
# restart (or a fresh `yarn build` for prod).

# ─── Client (NEXT_PUBLIC_*) ────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Optional. Set to "false" to hide all share-to-cloud affordances. Useful
# for deploys that don't have a database configured. Default: enabled.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUD_SYNC_ENABLED=true

# Optional. Absolute base URL for the cloud API. By default the client
# uses same-origin relative URLs (/api/matrix). Override only if you're
# pointing the SPA at a remote API during local development.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUD_API_URL=

# ─── Server (Route Handlers under app/api/) ───────────────────────────────

# Required to enable cloud sync. Use the local Docker container started
# by `yarn db:up`:
MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017

# Optional Mongo overrides. Defaults shown.
# MONGO_DB=riskmatrix
# MONGO_COLLECTION=matrices

# Optional limits. Defaults shown.
# MAX_CIPHERTEXT_BYTES=262144
# RETENTION_DAYS=90
# WRITE_RATE_LIMIT_PER_MIN=30
